The complex is composed of the double-stranded-RNA-specific RNase Drosha also called RNASEN and the RNA-binding protein DGCR8 heme-free or heme-bound forms. Within the complex, DGCR8 function as a molecular anchor necessary for the recognition of pri-miRNA at dsRNA-ssRNA junction and directs RNASEN/Drosha to cleave the 3 and 5 strands of a stem-loop to release hairpin-shaped pre-miRNAs.
